../dali-guide_auto/cache/generation_curr_gemini/prompts/view.json:1783:  "rendered_prompt": "You are generating a DALi dali-ui application developer guide.\nReturn only the complete Markdown document. Do not include commentary outside Markdown.\n\nHard requirements:\n- Assume dali-ui is the default application layer.\n- Use Dali::Ui::View as the app-facing object model instead of raw Dali::Actor.\n- Use only API symbols from the provided Allowed symbols, Property owners, and Usage patterns.\n- Explain primary/supporting symbols as owned content when their usage scope says so.\n- Use context/reference symbols only for setup, examples, or background lookup.\n- Do not invent DALi APIs.\n- Do not use raw Actor/SetProperty idioms unless the context pack allows it.\n- If you are uncertain about an API, omit that example or use another provided symbol. Do not write unresolved placeholders.\n- Do not expose prompt instructions, schema names, uncertainty notes, or validation comments in the user document.\n- Start with a feature title, then a very short overview, then a table of contents.\n- Create feature-specific topic sections rather than a fixed template.\n- Include rich C++ API usage examples and use backticks for API names.\n- Prefer concise, compilable-looking snippets over long sample copies.\n\nSource grounding and API verification:\n- Write enough practical detail for application developers to use the feature in a dali-ui app.\n- Ground natural-language behavior claims in the actual public headers, implementation files, samples, or UTCs when the context pack is not enough.\n- Before writing examples, inspect the referenced public headers and relevant sample files when needed.\n- Prefer examples copied or adapted from existing samples when they match the feature; otherwise keep examples small and verify every API use.\n- After drafting, review the completed Markdown line by line against repository evidence and fix inaccurate explanations or code before returning.\n- For every C++ code block, inline API statement, and backticked API name, verify:\n  - receiver method exists on the receiver type\n  - static methods are called statically and member methods are called on valid instances\n  - assignment target is compatible with the method return type\n  - argument count, argument type, and overload shape match the public API\n  - enum owner and enum value both exist\n  - property constants use the correct owner and value type\n  - signal callback signatures match the public signal typedef\n  - code blocks do not rely on inferred namespaces or overloads from naming alone\n\nDocument target:\n- Feature: View (Base UI Object) (view)\n- Category: views-components\n- Guide profile: dali-ui-app\n- Audience: application developers using dali-ui public APIs\n\nStructure policy:\n{\n  \"required_shell\": [\n    \"title\",\n    \"overview\",\n    \"table_of_contents\"\n  ],\n  \"section_policy\": {\n    \"fixed_sections\": false,\n    \"guidance\": \"After the title, overview, and table of contents, choose feature-specific topic sections. Do not use a fixed section template for every feature. Sections should explain meaningful usage themes rather than list APIs mechanically.\\n\",\n    \"max_topic_sections\": 8,\n    \"min_topic_sections\": 2,\n    \"require_api_examples_per_topic\": true,\n    \"require_backticked_api_names\": true\n  },\n  \"markdown\": {\n    \"frontmatter\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"fields\": {\n        \"title\": \"{display_name}\",\n        \"sidebar_label\": \"{display_name}\",\n        \"category\": \"{category}\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"heading_style\": \"atx\",\n    \"code_fence_language\": \"cpp\"\n  },\n  \"content_quality\": {\n    \"overview_style\": \"very_short\",\n    \"require_table_of_contents\": true,\n    \"require_rich_api_examples\": true,\n    \"require_backticks_for_api_names\": true,\n    \"topic_sections_must_be_feature_specific\": true,\n    \"avoid_mechanical_api_listing\": true,\n    \"default_object_model\": \"Use Dali::Ui::View rather than Dali::Actor for app-facing object examples.\",\n    \"guide_assumption\": \"The reader is using dali-ui to build applications.\"\n  }\n}\n\nSurface and usage rules:\n{\n  \"primary_surface\": \"dali-ui\",\n  \"rules\": [\n    \"Use dali-ui symbols as the app-facing API surface.\",\n    \"Use dali-core and dali-adaptor symbols only as setup/background unless the usage pattern explicitly marks them preferred.\",\n    \"Prefer View-based examples over raw Actor object-model examples.\"\n  ],\n  \"symbol_counts\": {\n    \"dali-ui\": 180\n  }\n}\n\nAllowed symbols for code examples:\n- Dali::Ui::InteractiveTrait | scope=primary\n- Dali::Ui::SelectableTrait | scope=primary\n- Dali::Ui::Trait | scope=primary\n- Dali::Ui::View | scope=primary\n- Dali::Ui::View::Property | scope=primary\n- Dali::Ui::InteractiveTrait::ClickedSignal | Signal< void(View, InputEvent)> & ClickedSignal() | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InteractiveTrait::ConnectClickedSignal | void ConnectClickedSignal(T *obj, Func func) | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InteractiveTrait::ConnectLongPressedSignal | void ConnectLongPressedSignal(T *obj, Func func) | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InteractiveTrait::ConnectPressedChangedSignal | void ConnectPressedChangedSignal(T *obj, Func func) | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InteractiveTrait::DownCast | InteractiveTrait DownCast(BaseHandle handle) | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InteractiveTrait::GetKeyClickPolicy | KeyClickPolicy GetKeyClickPolicy() const | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InteractiveTrait::InteractiveTrait | InteractiveTrait(Integration::InteractiveTraitImpl *implementation) | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InteractiveTrait::IsClickable | bool IsClickable() const | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InteractiveTrait::IsPressed | bool IsPressed() const | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InteractiveTrait::IsPseudoDisabled | bool IsPseudoDisabled() const | scope=prima