../dali-guide_auto/cache/generation/prompts/input-event.json:332:  "rendered_prompt": "You are generating a DALi dali-ui application developer guide.\nReturn only the complete Markdown document. Do not include commentary outside Markdown.\n\nHard requirements:\n- Assume dali-ui is the default application layer.\n- Use Dali::Ui::View as the app-facing object model instead of raw Dali::Actor.\n- Use only API symbols from the provided Allowed symbols, Property owners, and Usage patterns.\n- Explain primary/supporting symbols as owned content when their usage scope says so.\n- Use context/reference symbols only for setup, examples, or background lookup.\n- Do not invent DALi APIs.\n- Do not use raw Actor/SetProperty idioms unless the context pack allows it.\n- If you are uncertain about an API, omit that example or use another provided symbol. Do not write unresolved placeholders.\n- Do not expose prompt instructions, schema names, uncertainty notes, or validation comments in the user document.\n- Start with a feature title, then a very short overview, then a table of contents.\n- Create feature-specific topic sections rather than a fixed template.\n- Include rich C++ API usage examples and use backticks for API names.\n- Prefer concise, compilable-looking snippets over long sample copies.\n\nSource grounding and API verification:\n- Write enough practical detail for application developers to use the feature in a dali-ui app.\n- Ground natural-language behavior claims in the actual public headers, implementation files, samples, or UTCs when the context pack is not enough.\n- Before writing examples, inspect the referenced public headers and relevant sample files when needed.\n- Prefer examples copied or adapted from existing samples when they match the feature; otherwise keep examples small and verify every API use.\n- After drafting, review the completed Markdown line by line against repository evidence and fix inaccurate explanations or code before returning.\n- For every C++ code block, inline API statement, and backticked API name, verify:\n  - receiver method exists on the receiver type\n  - static methods are called statically and member methods are called on valid instances\n  - assignment target is compatible with the method return type\n  - argument count, argument type, and overload shape match the public API\n  - enum owner and enum value both exist\n  - property constants use the correct owner and value type\n  - signal callback signatures match the public signal typedef\n  - code blocks do not rely on inferred namespaces or overloads from naming alone\n\nDocument target:\n- Feature: Input Event (input-event)\n- Category: input-interaction\n- Guide profile: dali-ui-app\n- Audience: application developers using dali-ui public APIs\n\nStructure policy:\n{\n  \"required_shell\": [\n    \"title\",\n    \"overview\",\n    \"table_of_contents\"\n  ],\n  \"section_policy\": {\n    \"fixed_sections\": false,\n    \"guidance\": \"After the title, overview, and table of contents, choose feature-specific topic sections. Do not use a fixed section template for every feature. Sections should explain meaningful usage themes rather than list APIs mechanically.\\n\",\n    \"max_topic_sections\": 8,\n    \"min_topic_sections\": 2,\n    \"require_api_examples_per_topic\": true,\n    \"require_backticked_api_names\": true\n  },\n  \"markdown\": {\n    \"frontmatter\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"fields\": {\n        \"title\": \"{display_name}\",\n        \"sidebar_label\": \"{display_name}\",\n        \"category\": \"{category}\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"heading_style\": \"atx\",\n    \"code_fence_language\": \"cpp\"\n  },\n  \"content_quality\": {\n    \"overview_style\": \"very_short\",\n    \"require_table_of_contents\": true,\n    \"require_rich_api_examples\": true,\n    \"require_backticks_for_api_names\": true,\n    \"topic_sections_must_be_feature_specific\": true,\n    \"avoid_mechanical_api_listing\": true,\n    \"default_object_model\": \"Use Dali::Ui::View rather than Dali::Actor for app-facing object examples.\",\n    \"guide_assumption\": \"The reader is using dali-ui to build applications.\"\n  }\n}\n\nSurface and usage rules:\n{\n  \"primary_surface\": \"dali-ui\",\n  \"rules\": [\n    \"Use dali-ui symbols as the app-facing API surface.\",\n    \"Use dali-core and dali-adaptor symbols only as setup/background unless the usage pattern explicitly marks them preferred.\",\n    \"Prefer View-based examples over raw Actor object-model examples.\"\n  ],\n  \"symbol_counts\": {\n    \"dali-ui\": 12\n  }\n}\n\nAllowed symbols for code examples:\n- Dali::Ui::InputEvent | scope=primary\n- Dali::Ui::InputEvent::GetInputEventType | InputEventType GetInputEventType() const | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InputEvent::GetKeyEvent | const KeyEvent & GetKeyEvent() const | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InputEvent::GetLongPressGesture | const LongPressGesture & GetLongPressGesture() const | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InputEvent::GetTapGesture | const TapGesture & GetTapGesture() const | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InputEvent::GetTouchEvent | const TouchEvent & GetTouchEvent() const | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InputEvent::GetWheelEvent | const WheelEvent & GetWheelEvent() const | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InputEvent::InputEvent | InputEvent(Internal::InputEventImpl *impl) | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InputEvent::New | InputEvent New(const WheelEvent &originEvent) | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InputEvent::None | const InputEvent & None() | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InputEvent::operator= | InputEvent & operator=(const InputEvent &handle)=default | scope=primary_member\n- Dali::Ui::InputEvent::~InputEvent | ~InputEvent()=default | scope=primary_member\n\nProperty owner table:\n- (none)\n\nPreferred usage patterns:\n[\n  {\n    \"avoid_symbols\": [],\n    \"id\": \"input-event_basic_setup\",\n    \"intent\": \"Create and configure the primary object using public dali-ui APIs.\",\n    \"preferred_symbols\": [\n      \"Dali::Ui::InputEvent::New\"\n    ],\n    \"property_values\": [],\n    \"source\": \"static_api_shape\",\n    \"usage_note\": \"Prefer typed constructors and setters when available.\"\n  }\n]\n\nConstraints:\n{\n  \"avoid_idioms_unless_needed\": [\n    \"raw_actor_set_property\"\n  ],\n  \"forbidden_claims\": [],\n  \"prefer_idioms\": [\n    \"fluent_chaining\",\n    \"typed_setters\",\n    \"view_tree\"\n  ]\n}\n\nShort verified evidence snippets:\n- repos/dali-ui/samples/absolutelayout/absolutelayout-layout-direction-example.cpp:39 (sample, score=0.6)\n```cpp\n}\n\n  void Create(Application application)\n  {\n    Window window = application.GetWindow();\n    window.SetBackgroundColor(Color::WHITE);\n\n    // Root: AbsoluteLayout filling the window\n    mRoot = AbsoluteLayout::New()\n      .SetRequestedWidth(MATCH_PARENT)\n      .SetRequestedHeight(MATCH_PARENT);\n    // Red box: top-left corner, absolute position and size\n    View redBox = View::New();\n    redBox.SetBackgroundColor(Color::RED);\n    redBox.SetLayoutParams(AbsoluteLayoutParams::New()\n      .SetBounds(LayoutRect(50.0f, 50.0f, 50.0f, 50.0f)));\n    mRoot.Add(redBox);\n\n    // Green box: center area\n    View greenBox = View::New();\n    greenBox.SetBackgroundColor(Color::GREEN);\n    greenBox.SetLayoutParams(AbsoluteLayoutParams::New()\n      .SetBounds(LayoutRect(100.0f, 100.0f, 100.0f, 100.0f)));\n    mRoot.Add(greenBox);\n```\n\n- repos/dali-ui/samples/animation/animation-example.cpp:40 (sample, score=0.6)\n```cpp\n{\n    Window window = application.GetWindow();\n    window.SetBackgroundColor(Color::WHITE);\n\n    // Build a reusable fade-in spec\n    mFadeInSpec = View::NewAnimationSpec()\n      .Opacity(1.0f, 500_ms, AlphaFunction::EASE_IN_OUT);\n\n    window.Add(Layout::New()\n      .Children({\n        InteractiveView::New()\n          .SetBackgroundColor(UiColor(0xFF0000))\n          .SetRequestedWidth(200_spx)\n          .SetRequestedHeight(200_spx)\n          .ConnectClickedSignal(this, &AnimationExample::OnRedClicked)\n          .As(mRedBox),\n        InteractiveView::New()\n          .SetBackgroundColor(UiColor(0x0000FF))\n          .SetOpacity(0.3f)\n          .SetRequestedWidth(200_spx)\n          .SetRequestedHeight(200_spx)\n          .SetRequestedPositionX(220_spx)\n          .ConnectClickedSignal(this, &AnimationExample::OnBlueClicked)\n          .As(mBlueBox),\n```\n\nOptional source files to inspect if needed:\n[\n  {\n    \"kind\": \"sample\",\n    \"lookup_instruction\": \"Open this file only if more concrete usage evidence is needed.\",\n    \"matched_symbols\": [\n      \"InputEvent\",\n      \"New\"\n    ],\n    \"path\": \"repos/dali-ui/samples/absolutelayout/absolutelayout-layout-direction-example.cpp\",\n    \"relevance\": \"medium\",\n    \"score\": 0.6,\n    \"selection_reason\": \"symbol_and_path_match\",\n    \"snippet_end_line\": 118,\n    \"snippet_start_line\": 39\n  },\n  {\n    \"kind\": \"sample\",\n    \"lookup_instruction\": \"Open this file only if more concrete usage evidence is needed.\",\n    \"matched_symbols\": [\n      \"InputEvent\",\n      \"New\"\n    ],\n    \"path\": \"repos/dali-ui/samples/animation/animation-example.cpp\",\n    \"relevance\": \"medium\",\n    \"score\": 0.6,\n    \"selection_reason\": \"symbol_and_path_match\",\n    \"snippet_end_line\": 100,\n    \"snippet_start_line\": 40\n  },\n  {\n    \"kind\": \"sample\",\n    \"lookup_instruction\": \"Open this file only if more concrete usage evidence is needed.\",\n    \"matched_symbols\": [\n      \"InputEvent\",\n      \"New\"\n    ],\n    \"path\": \"repos/dali-ui/samples/color-controls/color-controls-example.cpp\",\n    \"relevance\": \"medium\",\n    \"score\": 0.6,\n    \"selection_reason\": \"symbol_and_path_match\",\n    \"snippet_end_line\": 103,\n    \"snippet_start_line\": 38\n  },\n  {\n    \"kind\": \"sample\",\n    \"lookup_instruction\": \"Open this fi